org.jenetics

Class Phenotype<G extends Gene<?,G>,C extends Comparable<? super C>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jenetics.Phenotype<G,C>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Phenotype<G,C>>, Runnable, Verifiable

    public final class Phenotype<G extends Gene<?,G>,C extends Comparable<? super C>>
extends Object
implements Comparable<Phenotype<G,C>>, Verifiable, Serializable, Runnable
    The Phenotype consists of a Genotype plus a fitness Function, where the fitness Function represents the environment where the Genotype lives. This class implements the Comparable interface, to define a natural order between two Phenotypes. The natural order of the Phenotypes is defined by its fitness value (given by the fitness Function. The Phenotype is immutable and therefore can't be changed after creation.

    The evaluation of the fitness function is performed lazily. Either by calling one of the fitness accessors (getFitness() or getRawFitness()) of through the evaluation methods run() or evaluate(). Since the Phenotype implements the Runnable interface, it is easily possible to perform the fitness function evaluation concurrently, by putting it into an ExecutorService.
